                    "company": "Rockfield Real Estate",
                    "description": "After my departure, IC Netherlands demerged from the International Campus Group and changed its name into Rockfield. The below description applies to IC Netherlands for the period I was working with the company.\n\nAs CFRO / statutory director I am responsible for finance, risk, tax, legal, compliance and IT.\n\nIC Netherlands is a Dutch real estate developer, investor and operator in student housing, young professional housing and co-living.\nCore features are high quality accommodation and working environments, inspiring community experiences and valuable extra services.\n\nIC Netherlands has around 8,000 apartments currently operating, under construction or in development. Our vision is to create great places to live while we have the ambition to grow up to 10,000 additional houses in the next years. We are also active in area development such as our current project \u2018Hyde Park\u2019 in the middle of the Metropole Region Amsterdam with a variety of 4,000 houses.\n\nIC Netherlands is a member of the International Campus Group, expanding throughout the whole of Europe. The International Campus Group is sponsored by Brookfield (TSX: BAM.A; NYSE: BAM and NASDAQ: BPY; TSX: BPY.UN).\n\nFrom January 2018 - August 2018 I also was Member of the FIZZ Fund Management Team in Luxembourg and Germany.\n\nThe 'FIZZ Student Housing Fund', named after International Campus's main brand 'THE FIZZ', is intended to operate as a long-term investment vehicle and will help accommodation specialist International Campus expand across Europe with its accomodation for students and young professionals.\n\nThe new fund is being seeded with four fully leased German properties containing 1,200 apartments in Berlin, Darmstadt, Frankfurt and Hanover. It is also acquiring four project developments with more than 1,600 apartments in Aachen, Frankfurt, Hamburg and Cologne. Preparations are underway for the acquisition of further investments.",
